"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390178","Home Office","false","2015-07-20","<p>The Government has agreed an operating budget of £17.9 million for the Inquiry in 2015/16. This was set out in Justice Goddard’s opening statement on 9 July, which is available in full on the independent Inquiry’s website at: www.csa-inquiry.independent.gov.uk.</p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2015-07-20T13:36:44.8Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390178/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390178/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390178/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-07-15","Child Sexual Abuse Independent Panel Inquiry","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what funding the Government has allocated to the Independent Inquiry into Child Sexual Abuse for this financial year.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","7352"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390179","Cabinet Office","false","2015-07-20","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2015-07-20T08:35:20.177Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390179/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390179/answer","PQ 7523.pdf ; PQ 7523.xlsx","PQ 7523.pdf ; PQ 7523.xlsx","UKSA Reply ; Table","UKSA Reply ; Table","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390179/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-07-15","Government Departments: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what proportion of staff of all Government departments were based in each region of the UK in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Simon Danczuk","Rochdale","Simon Danczuk","7523"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390180","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-20","<p>The cost considered by the Treasury to be disproportionate is £850. HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) are unable to provide an answer to PQ 5989 within proportionate costs as information stored on the tax credits system does not contain data on the amount of income tax and national insurance contributions, and to match this data would incur a cost of more than £850.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-07-20T15:24:57.667Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390180/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390180/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390180/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-15","Welfare Tax Credits","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 13 July 2015 to Question 5989, what estimate he has made of the cost of estimating the number of employees who receive more in tax credits than they pay in tax and national insurance contributions.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","7519"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390181","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-20","<p>The government has already made significant interventions on tobacco, both to protect revenue and to promote public health. This includes the extension of the tobacco duty escalator until the end of the current Parliament and the introduction of plain packaging for tobacco products from May 2016.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2015-07-20T13:49:33.983Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390181/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390181/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390181/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-15","Tobacco: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to paragraph 1.213 of the Summer Budget 2015 and paragraph 1.252 of the Autumn Statement 2014, what steps he plans to take to ask the tobacco industry to make a greater contribution to the costs imposed by smoking on society.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","7521"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390182","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-23","<p>Building our Future is an internal communications exercise in which HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) is having a conversation with its workforce about the future of the department, and how it can change its ways of working to meet customer needs and maximise tax compliance.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HMRC regularly engages with its stakeholders on the ways it is changing, which include investing in new digital services and data analysis to improve the customer experience and reduce tax error and fraud.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Its annual report for 2014-15 has just been published showing that HMRC has brought in record revenues of £517.7 billion last year, and sets out the department’s future development plans.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-07-23T14:52:22.477Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390182/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390182/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390182/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-15","Revenue and Customs","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will conduct a public consultation on the HM Revenue and Customs Building our Future programme.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","7449"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390183","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-20","<p>The European Commission is still considering the options for implementation of the requirement for a tracking and tracing system under the EU Tobacco Products Directive, and no potential systems will be evaluated until that work is concluded.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2015-07-20T13:50:52.927Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390183/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390183/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390183/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-15","Tobacco: Smuggling","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment HM Revenue and Customs has made of the effectiveness of the Codentify tracking and tracing system in preventing illicit trade in tobacco; and whether his Department plans to commission an independent assessment of the potential for that system to meet the requirement for a tracking and tracing system under the EU Tobacco Products Directive.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","7477"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390184","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-24","<p>The Government will make an announcement on next steps in due course.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-07-24T08:12:36.82Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390184/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390184/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390184/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-15","Money Advice Service","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to paragraph 2.10 of the Government's response to the independent review of the Money Advice Service, published in March 2015, when his Department plans to publish the terms of reference for and objectives of the review of the case for providing consumers with a breathing space.","false","Biography information for Yvonne Fovargue","Makerfield","Yvonne Fovargue","7490"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390185","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-20","<p>The Office for Budget Responsibility has assessed the measures relating to the housing market in the Summer Budget 2015. It estimates that they will have small and offsetting effects, and so it has not adjusted its forecast for house prices.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-07-20T15:42:44.027Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390185/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390185/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390185/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-15","Inheritance Tax","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the potential effects of the proposed increase in inheritance tax thresholds on property prices (a) nationally and (b) in each region of the UK.","false","Biography information for Liz Kendall","Leicester West","Liz Kendall","7483"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390186","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-24","<p>Any decisions on eligibility to NHS Tax Credits Exemption Certificates are matters for Health Ministers, including devolved administrations.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2015-07-24T12:11:21.663Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390186/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390186/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390186/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-15","NHS: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people will no longer be eligible for a NHS Tax Credit Exemption Certificate as a result of changes in the Summer Budget 2015.","false","Biography information for Owen Thompson","Midlothian","Owen Thompson","7459"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390187","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-21","<p>The Summer Budget 2015 announced significant additional investment of £800m in HM Revenue and Customs’ (HMRC’s) work on non‑compliance and tax evasion covering a range of areas.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>As well as announcing additional resource for these measures, the government is committed to providing HMRC with the funding it needs to maintain its current level of compliance performance, while making efficiencies.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-07-21T16:25:10.767Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390187/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390187/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390187/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-15","Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to paragraph 1.171 of the Summer Budget 2015, whether the £800 million investment in tackling tax non-compliance and evasion has been diverted from other business areas.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","7457"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390188","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-20","<p /> <p>To prevent young people slipping straight into a life on benefits, from April 2017 the Government will remove the automatic entitlement to housing support for new claims in Universal Credit from 18-21 year olds who are out of work. This will ensure young people in the benefits system face the same choices as young people who work and who may not be able to afford to leave home.</p><p> </p><p>We will ensure that vulnerable young people who are in need of support for their housing needs continue to receive it. Government will consider the impact in line with our legal obligations as part of that process.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-07-20T17:05:43.31Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390188/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390188/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390188/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-15","Disadvantaged","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, with reference to paragraph 2.111 of the Summer Budget 2015, who the vulnerable groups are; and what criteria he uses to decide those groups are vulnerable.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","7456"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390189","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-20","<p>The Government remains committed to spending 0.7% of gross national income (GNI) on official development assistance (ODA). The planned resource DEL expenditure for the Department for International Development (DFID) has decreased between March and Summer Budget by approximately £1bn because every year at Main Estimates in July DFID transfers ODA funding to other government departments to help meet the government’s overall international development objectives. This is purely a timing issue. The decrease in DFID’s resource budget for 2015/16 is reflected as increases to other government department’s resource budgets. For example, over £700m of the £1bn transfer from DFID to other departments made at Main Estimates is to FCO for the Conflict, Security and Stabilisation Fund (CSSF). The total planned DEL spend in 2015/16 across Government on ODA did not change between March and Summer budgets. DFID publishes actual ODA spent by departments, of which the latest provisional figures are available for 2014.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2015-07-20T16:33:31.503Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390189/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390189/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390189/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-15","Department for International Development: Departmental Expenditure Limits","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the answer of 14 July 2015 to Question 6473 and with reference to Tables 2.5 and 2.3 in the March and Summer Budget books, how the £1 billion reduction in the Department for International Development's Resource Department's Expenditure Limit has been reallocated.","false","Biography information for Mary Creagh","Wakefield","Mary Creagh","7359"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390190","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-20","<p>The Government remains committed to spending 0.7% of gross national income (GNI) on official development assistance (ODA). The planned resource DEL expenditure for the Department for International Development (DFID) has decreased between March and Summer Budget by approximately £1bn because every year at Main Estimates in July DFID transfers ODA funding to other government departments to help meet the government’s overall international development objectives. This is purely a timing issue. The decrease in DFID’s resource budget for 2015/16 is reflected as increases to other government department’s resource budgets and the total planned DEL spend in 2015/16 across Government on ODA did not change between March and Summer budgets.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2015-07-20T15:21:49.967Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390190/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390190/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390190/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-15","Department for International Development: Departmental Expenditure Limits","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the answer of 14 July 2015 to Question 6473 and with reference to Tables 2.5 and 2.3 in the March and Summer Budget books, why there is a £1 billion reduction in the Department for International Development's Resource Department's Expenditure Limit.","false","Biography information for Mary Creagh","Wakefield","Mary Creagh","7360"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390191","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-21","<p /> <p>Local Authorities have overall responsibility for how Discretionary Housing Payments (DHPs) are administered and paid, considering each case on its own merits. The Department publishes a DHP guidance manual and good practice guide to help Local Authorities identify those outline claimants who may require a DHP .</p><p> </p><p>No decisions have been made on allocations to local authorities for 2016/2017 and beyond. We consider the allocation of Discretionary Housing Payments each year, based on each local authority’s Housing Benefit expenditure and the local impact of reforms.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","7396","2015-07-21T13:02:13.753Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390191/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390191/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390191/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-15","Housing Benefit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, with reference to paragraph 1.153 of the Summer Budget 2015, if he will publish the criteria to decide who the most vulnerable housing benefit claimants are.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","7395"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390192","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-21"," <p>Local Authorities have overall responsibility for how Discretionary Housing Payments (DHPs) are administered and paid, considering each case on its own merits. The Department publishes a DHP guidance manual and good practice guide to help Local Authorities identify those outline claimants who may require a DHP .</p><p> </p><p>No decisions have been made on allocations to local authorities for 2016/2017 and beyond. We consider the allocation of Discretionary Housing Payments each year, based on each local authority’s Housing Benefit expenditure and the local impact of reforms.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","7395","2015-07-21T13:02:13.83Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390192/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390192/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390192/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-15","Housing Benefit: Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, with reference to paragraph 1.153 of the Summer Budget 2015, what estimate he has made of the proportion of the £800 million each local authority will receive.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","7396"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390193","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-23","<p>Ministers had regard to all relevant international obligations when formulating the welfare policies announced at the Budget and consider that these obligations have been complied with.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","7410 ; 7411","2015-07-23T13:43:23.083Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390193/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390193/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390193/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-15","Welfare Tax Credits","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment his Department has made of the compatibility of changes to (a) child tax credits, (b) working tax credit reductions, (c) working tax credit restrictions and (d) restriction of working tax credit to two children with the UN Convention on the Rights of the Child.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","7409"
