"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390196","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-21","<p>Ministers and officials have meetings with a wide variety of individuals and organisations in the public and private sectors as part of the process of policy development and delivery.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>As has been the case with previous administrations, it is not the Governments practice to provide details of such meetings.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-07-21T16:20:51.277Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390196/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390196/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390196/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-15","Compulsory Purchase: Capital Gains Tax","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what discussions he has had with the Secretary of State for Transport on reform of capital gains tax in relation to compulsory purchase.","false","Biography information for Michael Fabricant","Lichfield","Michael Fabricant","7383"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390197","Cabinet Office","false","2015-07-20","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2015-07-20T08:35:49.38Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390197/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390197/answer","PQ 7400 VH.pdf","PQ 7400 VH.pdf","UKSA Reply","UKSA Reply","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390197/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-07-15","Pay: Yorkshire and the Humber","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what estimate he has made of the number of people between the ages of 16 and 24 in (a) West Yorkshire and (b) Leeds earning less than £7.20 per hour.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","7400"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390198","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-20","<p /> <p>· The Budget provided additional funding from April 2017, rising from £60m in 2017/18 to £100m a year in 2020/21.</p><p> </p><p>· Further details will be set out in the autumn.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-07-20T15:38:08.29Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390198/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390198/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390198/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-15","Employment and Support Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the financial statement by the Chancellor of the Exchequer on 8 July 2015, Official Report, column 334, what the value will be of the new funding to provide additional support to help employment and support allowance claimants return to work; and what form this additional support will take.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","7292"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390199","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-22","<p>Employer investment in skills has been a problem since the 1990s and it needs to change. Large companies will now have direct control via the digital apprenticeship voucher and firms that are committed to training will be able to get back more than the put in. Further details will be set at the Spending Review following a formal engagement with business.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2015-07-22T15:09:19.673Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390199/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390199/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390199/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-15","Apprentices: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what criteria he plans to apply when assessing which businesses will be required to pay the new apprenticeship levy.","false","Biography information for Michelle Thomson","Edinburgh West","Michelle  Thomson","7312"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390200","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-22","<p>The Barnett formula will apply to spending on apprenticeships in England in the usual way. Skills policy is a devolved area so the DAs will have complete flexibility over how to support businesses. Further details will be set at the Spending Review following a formal engagement with business.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2015-07-22T15:07:11.677Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390200/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390200/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390200/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-15","Apprentices: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will make an estimate of the number of businesses in (a) Scotland and (b) the UK that will be required to pay the new apprenticeship levy.","false","Biography information for Michelle Thomson","Edinburgh West","Michelle  Thomson","7313"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390201","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-22","<p>The government has committed to 3 million apprenticeship starts over the Parliament. The new levy on large employers will fund the step change needed in starts and quality. Further details will be set at the Spending Review following a formal engagement with business.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2015-07-22T15:08:10.903Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390201/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390201/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390201/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-15","Apprentices: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of level of revenue that will be raised from the new apprenticeship levy; and what additional funding he plans will be available for apprenticeships in England.","false","Biography information for Michelle Thomson","Edinburgh West","Michelle  Thomson","7314"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390202","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-22","<p>Spending on apprenticeships in England will flow through the Barnett formula in the usual way. Skills policy is a devolved area, so the Scottish Government will continue to have complete flexibility over how to support businesses through training and apprenticeships.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2015-07-22T15:06:09.087Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390202/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390202/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390202/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-15","Apprentices: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether he plans to make available to the Scottish Government additional resources as a result of plans to increase funding for apprenticeships in England.","false","Biography information for Michelle Thomson","Edinburgh West","Michelle  Thomson","7315"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390203","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-24","<p>We recognise there will always be individuals who need extra support using digital channels and we acknowledge that the continued growth and development of our digital services cannot be at the expense of people who cannot use them, do not have the technology, or who struggle to use them. Our digital strategy incorporates principles for supporting people who need help and those who are digitally excluded.</p><p> </p><p>The strategy can be found at:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/hmrc-digital-strategy-2014/hmrc-digital-strategy-2014</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2015-07-24T13:24:48.61Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390203/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390203/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390203/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-15","Revenue and Customs","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the effect of moving HM Revenue and Customs services online on people using such services who are without access to the technology required for online access.","false","Biography information for Charlotte Leslie","Bristol North West","Charlotte Leslie","7332"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390204","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-23","<p>The Government is making changes to tax credits and Universal Credit which will help put welfare spending on a more sustainable path. The Government wants to move from a low wage, high tax, and high welfare society to a higher wage, lower tax, and lower welfare society. That means more emphasis on supporting hardworking families on low incomes by reducing income tax through increases in the personal allowance and increasing wages, than on topping up low wages through tax credits.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Government is focusing the tax credit system on those who need it most. Prior to 2010, 9 out of 10 families with children were eligible for tax credits and reforms in the previous Parliament reduced this to 6 out of 10. The measures announced in Summer Budget 2015 will result in 5 out of 10 families with children being eligible for tax credits support.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HMRC publishes information on the number of families receiving tax credits. The most recent available data is for 2013/14 and can be found here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/child-and-working-tax-credits-statistics-finalised-annual-awards-2013-to-2014" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/child-and-working-tax-credits-statistics-finalised-annual-awards-2013-to-2014</a>.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>This information can be found in Table 1.1.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2015-07-23T13:40:41.29Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390204/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390204/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390204/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-15","Welfare Tax Credits","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people previously in receipt of tax credits will no longer receive them following changes covered in the Summer Budget 2015.","false","Biography information for Owen Thompson","Midlothian","Owen Thompson","7188"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390205","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-23","<p>Table 1.8 in the Summer Budget 2015 used OBR CPI forecasts as the measure of inflation.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-07-23T14:53:10.07Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390205/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390205/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390205/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-15","Personal Income","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to Table 1.8 of the Summer Budget 2015, which Office for Budget Responsibility inflation forecast was used to calculate the data in that table.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","7196"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390206","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-07-22","<p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>Currently, the Apprentice rate applies to apprentices over the age of 25 where they are in their first year of their apprenticeship. They then qualify for the age appropriate rate.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>We will be implementing the National Living Wage through amendments to the National Minimum Wage regulations, in time for April 2016. We will consider how the Living Wage applies to the Apprentice rate as part of this process.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2015-07-22T13:18:11.24Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390206/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390206/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390206/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-07-15","Apprentices: Living Wage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, whether he plans for the National Living Wage announced in his Summer Budget 2015 to apply to apprentices over the age of 25.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","7222"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390207","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-20","<p>The new Joint Security Fund will grow to £1.5bn by the end of this Parliament and will fund key capabilities in Defence and the Intelligence Agencies, providing further support for the UK to defend itself against the threats it faces. The profile of this fund will not be determined until the conclusion of the Spending Review and Strategic Defence and Security Review this autumn.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2015-07-20T16:11:14.657Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390207/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390207/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390207/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-15","Defence: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much funding will be allocated to the Joint Security Fund in each year up to 2020.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","7223"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390208","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-22","<p>Employer investment in skills has been a problem since the 1990s and it needs to change. Large companies will now have direct control via the digital apprenticeship voucher and firms that are committed to training will be able to get back more than the put in. Further details will be set at the Spending Review following a formal engagement with business.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2015-07-22T15:04:56.697Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390208/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390208/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390208/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-07-15","Apprentices: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to the Summer Budget 2015, what criteria he plans to use to determine which employers are affected by the apprenticeship levy.","false","Biography information for Chris Bryant","Rhondda","Chris Bryant","7240"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390209","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-07-21","<p>According to the English Housing Survey the following people aged under 25 were tenants in social housing in England in 2013-14: a) 206,000 women; b) 71,000 men; c) 56,000 black or ethnic minority; d) 215,000 white British; and, e) 38,000 disabled.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-07-21T16:59:48.537Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390209/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390209/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390209/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-07-15","Social Rented Housing: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many social housing tenants aged under 25 are (a) women, (b) men, (c) black and minority ethnic, (d) white British and (e) disabled.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","7333"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390210","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-07-21","<p>The impact of the new National Living Wage on local authority finances will be considered during the Spending Review as part of an overall assessment of spending pressures on local authorities. <br><br>We believe that local authorities should be able to manage the reduction in rents paid by social tenants, but will be engaging with them as they develop their plans to meet their reductions. We will consider later in the year whether any council needs any particular support to manage their business plans, above that already provided through sector-led support.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2015-07-21T16:39:57.25Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390210/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390210/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390210/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-07-15","Local Government Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will make it his policy to provide additional funding to support local authorities' to take account of changes in the Summer Budget 2015 which will (a) increase the minimum wage and (b) reduce the rents paid by social tenants.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","7334"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390211","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-07-21","Income to the Housing Revenue Account is recorded in the Revenue Accounts and published here: https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/local-authority-revenue-expenditure-and-financing The Department does not produce forecasts of local authorities rents.","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-07-21T16:26:25.243Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390211/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390211/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390211/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-07-15","Social Rented Housing: Rents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, (a) how much each local authority in England received in rent from its social housing tenants in each year from 2010 to 2015 and (b) how much each local authority in England will receive in rent from its social housing tenants in 2019-20 following the announcement in the Summer Budget 2015 of a one per cent cut in each year of this Parliament.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","7335"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390212","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-07-20","<p>The Secretary of State's decision letter of 14 July 2014 sets out in full the evidence he took into account in reaching his decision on this appeal. That letter is available to view at</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/recovered-appeal-former-aerodrome-north-orbital-road-upper-colne-valley-hertfordshire-ref-2109433-14-july-2014.</p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","7329","2015-07-20T16:10:05.853Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390212/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390212/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390212/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-07-15","Railways: Elstree","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 7 July 2015 to Question 4550, what estimate his Department made of the (a) cost and (b) timescale of work needing to be carried out on the Elstree Tunnels prior to his approval of the planning application for the Radlett Strategic Rail Freight Terminal.","false","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden","7328"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390213","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-07-20","<p>The Secretary of State's decision letter of 14 July 2014 sets out in full the evidence he took into account in reaching his decision on this appeal. That letter is available to view at</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/recovered-appeal-former-aerodrome-north-orbital-road-upper-colne-valley-hertfordshire-ref-2109433-14-july-2014.</p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","7328","2015-07-20T16:10:05.933Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390213/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390213/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390213/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-07-15","Railways: Elstree","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 7 July 2015 to Question 4550, what estimate his Department made of what the source of the funding would be for the work required on the Elstree Tunnels prior to his approval of the planning application for the Radlett Strategic Rail Freight Terminal.","false","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden","7329"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390214","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-07-20","<p>In 2013-14, 15% of social renters in London were non-UK/Irish nationals.<br><br>If a tenant is not resident in the UK, we would expect a social landlord to take action to recover the property and allocate it to someone in need on the waiting list.</p><p> </p><p>Statutory guidance for local councils issued in 2013 will ensure that only people who have lived in the area for two years or more are able to put their name down on the housing waiting list.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-07-20T15:59:13.797Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390214/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390214/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390214/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-07-15","Social Rented Housing: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will estimate the number of social homes in London occupied by non-UK residents.","false","Biography information for Mr Douglas Carswell","Clacton","Mr Douglas Carswell","7289"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390215","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-07-21","<p>The Government is committed to providing local government with the support it needs to meet future challenges and to continue to improve services that local people want to see.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is also committed to devolving powers from Whitehall to rural as well as urban areas. My rt. hon. Friend, the Prime Minister announced on 16 July historic new powers for Cornwall as part of the first devolution deal for an English county. This includes bus franchising, integration of health and social care, and greater influence on skills and investment funding. As with cities the Government expect to negotiate further devolution deals with rural areas over the coming months and years.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, in 2015-16 the Rural Services Delivery Grant was increased by £4 million to £15.5 million to recognise the challenges the most rural local authorities face in delivering services.</p><p> </p><p>The Government has also provided significant funding to support the sector to improve services (£23.4 million in 2015-16). The sector can shape, through the Local Government Association, how this funding is used to support all authorities, including rural ones.</p><p> </p><p>Furthermore, the productivity plan, published on 10 July, set out our continued commitment to shifting the delivery and design of services to the local level, promoting the use of shared services and increasing the use of digital technology and data sharing to enable services to reduce costs and increase outputs. We will work with areas on these issues ahead of the forthcoming Spending Review.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2015-07-21T16:53:11.79Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390215/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390215/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390215/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-07-15","Local Government Services: Rural Areas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what steps he is taking to improve service delivery by local authorities in rural areas; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","7268"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390216","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-07-21","<p>The table below shows the average time for an appeal to be heard, following validation, in the last five years.<br><br>Fiscal Year Weeks<br><br>2010-11 14.3<br>2011-12 12.4<br>2012-13 14.8<br>2013-14 16<br>2014-15 13.8</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-07-21T16:55:24.497Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390216/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390216/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390216/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-07-15","Planning Permission: Appeals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what the average time was for an appeal to the Planning Inspectorate to be heard following validation in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Richard Fuller","Bedford","Richard Fuller","7406"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390217","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-07-21","<p>The Homelessness Gold Standard programme is a voluntary, sector-led initiative delivered by the National Practitioner Support Service and hosted by Winchester City Council to support local authorities to improve the effectiveness of homelessness prevention services. We provided £2.2 million between 2013/14 and 2014/15 to kick start the programme and help to get the scheme off the ground. Nearly all councils in England have signed up to working toward the Gold Standard, thus enabling them to access the support and good practice the programme offers. There are no current plans for future spending.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2015-07-21T16:47:13.897Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390217/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390217/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390217/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-07-15","Homelessness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what plans he has for the future of the homelessness gold standard programme.","false","Biography information for Sir Charles Walker","Broxbourne","Mr Charles Walker","7389"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390218","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-07-21","<p>The attached table shows the average time taken for all Section 78 Planning appeals and Householder appeals to be validated in the last (a) 12 months and (b) five years.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-07-21T16:32:23.763Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390218/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390218/answer","PQ 7405.docx","PQ 7405.docx","Table - Planning Appeals","Table - Planning Appeals","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390218/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-07-15","Planning Permission: Appeals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what the average time was for an appeal to the Planning Inspectorate to be validated in each of the last (a) 12 months and (b) five years.","false","Biography information for Richard Fuller","Bedford","Richard Fuller","7405"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390219","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-07-21","<p>Figures are not available for those aged under 18 or between 18 and 21 years old.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2015-07-21T16:41:40.497Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390219/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390219/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390219/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-07-15","Homelessness: West Yorkshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many people are designated as homeless in (a) West Yorkshire and (b) Leeds; and what proportion of them are aged (i) under 18 and (ii) between 18 and 21.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","7394"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390220","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-07-20","<p>Since being appointed on 20 May 2015 I have, in my role as Community Pubs Minister, met senior representatives of the British Beer and Pub Association, CAMRA, Punch Taverns, the Association of Licensed Multiple Retailers, the British Institute of Innkeeping and the Perceptions Group to discuss a wide range of issues affecting the pubs and brewing sector.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2015-07-20T16:33:17.1Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390220/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390220/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390220/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-07-15","Public Houses","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, whether the Minister for Local Government has met (a) pub-owning companies, (b) the British Beer & Pub Association, (c) CAMRA, (d) the Pubs Advisory Services, (e) Fair Pint and (f) other people or bodies to discuss the statutory pubs code and the Government's policy towards pubs since 7 May 2015.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","7486"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390221","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-07-22","<p>Of the £30m of in-year savings announced by the Chancellor: a) £24m related to underspends across the Group; b) there was a £1.5m reduction to core budgets; and, c) a £4.5m reduction in funding to arm's length bodies.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-07-22T09:29:35.957Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390221/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390221/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390221/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-07-15","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: Public Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, with reference to HM Treasury's press release, Chancellor announces £4.5 billion of measures to bring down debt, published on 4 June 2015, what amount of the £30 million additional savings from his Department will consist of (a) underspends within the DCMS group, (b) reduction in core budget and (c) reductions in funding to arms-length bodies.","false","Biography information for Chris Bryant","Rhondda","Chris Bryant","7431"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390222","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-07-23","<p>Forecasts of projected BBC expenditure, before the Summer Budget 2015, were made in the Office for Budget Responsibility’s Economic and Fiscal Outlook, published in March 2015. It can be found using the following link:</p><p><a href="http://cdn.budgetresponsibility.independent.gov.uk/March2015EFO_18-03-webv1.pdf" target="_blank">http://cdn.budgetresponsibility.independent.gov.uk/March2015EFO_18-03-webv1.pdf</a></p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-07-23T16:48:53.803Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390222/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390222/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390222/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-07-15","BBC","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what estimate his Department made of projected BBC expenditure in each of the next years before the Summer Budget 2015.","false","Biography information for Chris Bryant","Rhondda","Chris Bryant","7342"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390223","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-07-24","<p>The Department does not collect this information. However, the Office for National Statistics Labour Force Survey does collect data on the number of &quot;journalists, newspaper and periodical editors&quot; in employment. The figures for the last 5 years can be found in the table below.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>2014</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Journalists, newspaper and periodical editors</p></td><td><p>63,000</p></td><td><p>62,000</p></td><td><p>65,000</p></td><td><p>70,000</p></td><td><p>60,000</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p>Source: The Office for National Statistics Labour Force Survey, Employment by Occupation</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-07-24T12:02:13.37Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390223/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390223/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390223/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-07-15","Journalism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what information his Department holds on the number of journalists employed (a) in total and (b) at national newspapers in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Chris Bryant","Rhondda","Chris Bryant","7343"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390224","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-07-21","<p>Decisions on any investment in the rollout of superfast broadband beyond 95% will be taken as part of the forthcoming Spending Review.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-07-21T16:32:49.503Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390224/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390224/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390224/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-07-15","Broadband","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, whether any of the funding for rollout of superfast broadband top sliced from the television licence fee has been retained for phase 3 of the rollout programme.","false","Biography information for Chris Bryant","Rhondda","Chris Bryant","7341"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390225","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-07-22","<p>We are seeking views on the practicalities of enforcement of modernising the licence fee in order to cover public service broadcast catch-up TV as part of BBC Charter Review public consultation published on Thursday 16 July.</p><p> </p><p>The current TV Licence Fee enforcement regime, which includes live or nearly live broadcast television content on any electronic device including via iPlayer, has been reviewed independently. The report has been published and is available via this link: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/445212/166926_Perry_Review_Text-L-PB.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/445212/166926_Perry_Review_Text-L-PB.pdf</a></p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-07-22T09:28:15.847Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390225/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390225/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390225/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-07-15","BBC: Video on Demand","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what information he holds on how the BBC will enforce payment of the licence fee by people watching iPlayer.","false","Biography information for Chris Bryant","Rhondda","Chris Bryant","7340"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390226","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-07-22","<p>We welcome publication of Ofcom's review and statement on Public Service Broadcasting. We will be considering the evidence and recommendations alongside the Charter Review process and in light of responses to our consultation on balance of payments and electronic programme guides.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-07-22T09:33:07.957Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390226/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390226/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390226/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-07-15","Public Service Broadcasting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps he plans to take in response to Ofcom's Third Review of Public Sector Broadcasting, published in July 2015.","false","Biography information for Chris Bryant","Rhondda","Chris Bryant","7339"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390227","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-07-23","<p>The Museum of London's aspiration to move to a new site was supported by the Government at the Summer Budget. However, at this stage there are no plans to provide direct Government funding.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-07-23T16:45:28.39Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390227/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390227/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390227/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-07-15","Museum of London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, with reference to paragraph 1.325 of the Summer Budget 2015, whether the Government plans to provide financial support for the move of the Museum of London.","false","Biography information for Chris Bryant","Rhondda","Chris Bryant","7338"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390228","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-07-24","<p>The letter was not received and a duplicate has been requested.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-07-24T10:19:17.33Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390228/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390228/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390228/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-07-15","Members: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, when the Minister of State for Culture and the Digital Economy plans to respond to the letter to him of 29 June 2015 from the hon. Member for Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey.","false","Biography information for Drew Hendry","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Drew Hendry","7243"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390229","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-07-21","<p>I met with John Swinney MSP, Deputy First Minister in the Scottish Government on 8 June 2015. 4G mobile coverage was not discussed at that meeting. The Minister for Culture and the Digital Economy has met with the Secretary of State for Scotland and discussed options of mobile coverage including indoor 4G coverage to 98% of all premises by the end of 2017.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-07-21T16:48:39.413Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390229/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390229/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390229/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-07-15","4G: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what recent discussions he has had with (a) the Secretary of State  for Scotland and (b) Ministers in the Scottish Government on the provision of 4G mobile telephone coverage in Scotland.","false","Biography information for Margaret Ferrier","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Margaret Ferrier","7219"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390230","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-20","<p>The projection for the target strength of the Royal Air Force Regiment of the Royal Air Force for the current and subsequent four financial years is as follows:</p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td><p><strong>2015-16</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2016-17</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2017-18</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2018-19</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2019-20</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total</p></td><td><p>2,290</p></td><td><p>2,160</p></td><td><p>2,130</p></td><td><p>2,210</p></td><td><p>2,230</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-07-20T16:16:49.95Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390230/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390230/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390230/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-07-15","RAF Regiment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what projections his Department has made of the target strength of the Royal Air Force Regiment of the Royal Air Force in each of the next five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","7224"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390231","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-21","<p>The civilian operating costs of the Force Development Training Centre at Fairbourne in financial year 2014-2015 were some £169,000. The costs for financial year 2015-2016, from 1 April to 30 June 2015, were some £38,000.</p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-07-21T15:38:21.717Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390231/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390231/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390231/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-07-15","Air Force: Fairbourne","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the civilian operational costs were of the Force Development Training Centre at Fairbourne in (a) 2015-16 and (b) 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","7230"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390232","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-21","<p>The recommendations from the RAF's Review of Force Development and Adventurous Training are being carefully considered to ensure that this training provides the optimum support solution for Defence. The outcome of the Review will be announced in due course.</p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-07-21T15:38:51.377Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390232/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390232/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390232/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-07-15","Air Force: Fairbourne","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when he plans to reach a decision on the future of the Force Development Training Centre at Fairbourne.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","7229"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390233","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-21","<p>The Ministry of Defence has plans to modernise both Challenger 2 and Warrior to retain the Army's capability to field these vehicles to 2035 and 2040 respectively.</p><p>A contract was placed in October 2011 for the Warrior Capability Sustainment Programme which will include an improved turret with a new stabilised 40mm cannon and a tailored armour mounting system. The Challenger 2 Life Extension Programme is currently in the concept phase and this will address the key obsolescence issues on the vehicle.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-07-21T16:05:40.197Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390233/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390233/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390233/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-07-15","Armoured Fighting Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans he has to modernise the (a) Challenger II tank and (b) Warrior armoured fighting vehicle; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","7350"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390234","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-23","<p>A copy of the 2014-15 Chart of Account Manual will be placed in the Library of the House. I expect the 2015-16 Chart of Account Manual to be available within the next two months and a copy will also be placed in the Library.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2015-07-23T13:43:11.227Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390234/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390234/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390234/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-07-15","Ministry of Defence: Public Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will place in the Library copies of his Department's Chart of Account for 2014-15 and 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","7269"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390235","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-20","<p>The current planning assumptions for the out of service dates for Typhoon are: Tranche 1, 2019; Tranche 2, 2030; and Tranche 3, 2030. The current planning assumption for the out of service date for Tornado GR4 is 2019.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-07-20T16:04:57.947Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390235/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390235/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390235/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-07-15","Military Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the out of service date is for the (a) Typhoon Tranche 1, (b) Typhoon Tranche 2, (c) Typhoon Tranche 3 and (d) Tornado GR4.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","7270"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390236","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-21","<p>The Ministry of Defence is currently considering an unsolicited proposal from General Dynamics for an extension to the existing initial in-service support arrangements for the Scout Specialist Vehicle during its manufacture period. This extension might result in General Dynamics Land Systems UK taking the decision to transfer some vehicle assembly to the UK.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-07-21T16:07:01.23Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390236/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390236/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390236/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-07-15","Armoured Fighting Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will take steps to establish a Scout specialist vehicle assembly line in the UK; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","7271"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390237","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-21","<p>The Ministry of Defence is procuring 589 Scout Specialist Vehicles.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-07-21T15:30:55.353Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390237/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390237/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390237/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-07-15","Armoured Fighting Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many Scout specialist vehicles he plans to procure; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","7272"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390238","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-20","<p>As we move forward in the Demonstration Phase for the Type 26 Global Combat Ship, work continues to determine the detailed manning requirements for these vessels.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-07-20T16:03:44.7Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390238/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390238/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390238/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-07-15","Type 23 Frigates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the planned crew complement by (a) rank and (b) specialisation is for the Type 23 Global Combat Ship.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","7267"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390239","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-21","<p>The overall number of Joint Strike Fighter aircraft to be procured will be considered during the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015.</p><p> </p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-07-21T15:31:32.943Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390239/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390239/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390239/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-07-15","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many Lightning IIs he intends to procure; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","7349"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390240","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-20","<p>The Bechtel and CH2M Hill Managed Service Provider (MSP) contracts are based on a standard working week of 40 hours and the PwC MSP contract has a 37 hour working week, although actual weekly hours worked will depend upon the needs of the programme.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-07-20T16:05:46.47Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390240/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390240/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390240/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-07-15","Defence Equipment and Support","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many working hours each week are provided by staff from (a) Bechtel, (b) PwC and (c) CH2M Hill under the managed service provider contracts to facilitate Defence Equipment and Support's transition to a trading entity.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","7355"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390241","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-20","<p>Yes. The target for the size of the Army for each year up to 2020 is around 82,000.</p><p> </p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier",,"2015-07-20T15:45:56.457Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390241/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390241/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390241/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-07-15","Army","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 9 June 2015 to Question 1249, whether his Department has targets for army strength for each year up to 2020.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","7353"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390242","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-20","<p>The number and the grade of staff from Bechtel, PwC and CH2M Hill engaged in Defence Equipment and Support (DE&amp;S) varies across the period of the Managed Service Provider contracts. The total number and current breakdown of staff by grade is as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td><p><strong>Bechtel</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>CH2M Hill</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Level 3</p></td><td><p>3</p></td><td><p>2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Level 2</p></td><td><p>7</p></td><td><p>7</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Level 1</p></td><td><p>62</p></td><td><p>58</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>72</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>67</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td><p><strong>PwC</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Partner</p></td><td><p>3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Director</p></td><td><p>5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Senior Manager</p></td><td><p>12</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Manager</p></td><td><p>24</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Senior Associate</p></td><td><p>20</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Associate</p></td><td><p>7</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>71</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td colspan="2"> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td colspan="2"> </td><td colspan="2"> </td></tr><tr><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td></tr></tbody></table><p>The different &quot;levels&quot; for Bechtel and CH2M HILL reflect the internal grading systems of those companies. Level 3 is the most senior and refers to a Partner, or professional person of similar seniority.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","7356","2015-07-20T16:16:11.867Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390242/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390242/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390242/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-07-15","Defence Equipment and Support","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many staff from (a) Bechtel, (b) PwC and (c) CH2M Hill have been seconded to work full-time in Defence Equipment and Support as part of the managed service provider contracts to facilitate its transition to a trading entity.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","7358"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390243","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-20","<p>The number and the grade of staff from Bechtel, PwC and CH2M Hill engaged in Defence Equipment and Support (DE&amp;S) varies across the period of the Managed Service Provider contracts. The total number and current breakdown of staff by grade is as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td><p><strong>Bechtel</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>CH2M Hill</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Level 3</p></td><td><p>3</p></td><td><p>2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Level 2</p></td><td><p>7</p></td><td><p>7</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Level 1</p></td><td><p>62</p></td><td><p>58</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>72</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>67</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td><p><strong>PwC</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Partner</p></td><td><p>3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Director</p></td><td><p>5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Senior Manager</p></td><td><p>12</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Manager</p></td><td><p>24</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Senior Associate</p></td><td><p>20</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Associate</p></td><td><p>7</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>71</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td colspan="2"> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td colspan="2"> </td><td colspan="2"> </td></tr><tr><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td></tr></tbody></table><p>The different &quot;levels&quot; for Bechtel and CH2M HILL reflect the internal grading systems of those companies. Level 3 is the most senior and refers to a Partner, or professional person of similar seniority.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","7358","2015-07-20T16:16:11.993Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390243/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390243/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390243/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-07-15","Defence Equipment and Support","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many staff in each salary band from (a) Bechtel, (b) PwC and (c) CH2M Hill are working under the managed service provider contracts to facilitate Defence Equipment and Support's transition to a trading entity.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","7356"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390244","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-20","<p>The Bechtel and CH2M Hill contracts are due to run for three and a half years with the option of two one-year extensions. Their combined value is approximately £215 million over the course of the initial term.</p><p>The PwC contract is due to run for three years with the option of two one-year extensions. Its value is approximately £43 million over the initial three years.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-07-20T16:11:34.867Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390244/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390244/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390244/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-07-15","Defence Equipment and Support","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the (a) length and (b) value is of his Department's managed service provider contracts with (i) Bechtel, (ii) PwC and (iii) CH2M Hill related to Defence Equipment and Support's transition to a trading entity.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","7351"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390245","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-20","<p>As well as the annual real terms increase in the defence budget announced in the summer budget, up to an additional £1.5 billion per year by 2020-21 will be made available for the Ministry of Defence and Security and Intelligence agencies. The process of allocation will be determined through the Strategic Defence and Security Review and Spending Review which conclude later this year.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2015-07-20T16:19:50.127Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390245/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390245/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390245/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-07-15","Defence: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much his Department has been allocated from the Joint Security Fund in each year up to 2020.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","7367"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390246","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-21","<p>Defence Equipment &amp; Support (DE&amp;S) does not hold details of the number of consultants employed. DE&amp;S negotiates contracts with consultancy companies to deliver a specific output at an agreed price. It does not specify the number of consultants to be employed to deliver those outputs as this is a matter for the contractor.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-07-21T16:06:29.513Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390246/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390246/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390246/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-07-15","Defence Equipment and Support","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many external consultants are employed in Defence Equipment and Support by his Department.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","7384"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390247","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-20","<p>As at 1 April 2015, 7,700 civilian and military personnel worked for Defence Equipment and Support at its Abbey Wood site. Of this number, 880 personnel have been military trained.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-07-20T16:01:40.11Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390247/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390247/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390247/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-07-15","Defence Equipment and Support","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many staff work for Defence Equipment and Support at the Abbey Wood site; and how many of those staff are militarily trained.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","7385"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390248","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-20","<p>On current plans the requirements for Trained Regular Royal Marines<sup>[1]</sup> is as follows:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>April 2015</p></td><td><p>6,600</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>April 2016</p></td><td><p>6,600</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>April 2017</p></td><td><p>6,600</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>April 2018</p></td><td><p>6,600</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>April 2019</p></td><td><p>6,600</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>April 2020</p></td><td><p>6,600</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>[1] This answer is based on the Navy Planning Liability which is used for planning purposes within the Royal Navy and the figures are rounded to the nearest 100.</p><p> </p><p>The numbers exclude a number of Royal Marine specialisations such as Chefs; Medical Assistants; Aircrewman Commando and Pilots, included with Royal Navy branches for planning purposes.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-07-20T16:15:31.783Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390248/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390248/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390248/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-07-15","Marines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what projections his Department has made of the target strength of the Royal Marines in each of the next five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","7368"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390249","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-07-21","<p>Tradition and precedents sets out that Remembrance Sunday commemorates the contribution of British and Commonwealth military and civilian servicemen and women in the two World Wars and later conflicts. There are no plans to change the current representation.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2015-07-21T16:50:41.293Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390249/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390249/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390249/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-07-15","Remembrance Day","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what plans the Government has to include representations from the Polish forces and other countries at the 2015 Remembrance Day ceremony at the Cenotaph; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Henry Bellingham","North West Norfolk","Mr Henry Bellingham","7432"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390250","Department for Education","false","2015-07-23","<p>I have recently met representatives of communities and schools in which these languages are spoken, to hear their concerns and consider how we can work with the awarding organisations and Ofqual to maintain a range of languages at GCSE and A level, including Turkish, modern Greek and other languages.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The number of pupils studying for a modern language GCSE has increased by 20% since 2010 due to the introduction of the English Baccalaureate. Studying a foreign language provides an opening to other cultures, fosters pupils’ curiosity and deepens their understanding of the world. It also equips pupils to study and work in other countries. There are considerable benefits to learning a second language and the government is keen to see the range of languages at GCSE and A level preserved.</p><p> </p><p>The Department for Education does not promote the teaching of one foreign language over another and has not made an assessment of the benefits of pupils learning Turkish, modern Greek or other community languages.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The department is currently working with awarding organisations and Ofqual to consider how best to enable as wide a range of languages as possible to be maintained at GCSE and A level. The government has been clear that it wants to see all pupils provided with the opportunity to take a core set of academic subjects, including modern foreign languages.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Secretary of State wrote to exam boards in April 2015 to express her concern about awarding organisations’ decision to stop awarding qualifications in some languages, and to ask those organisations to work with Ofqual on the future of these qualifications. We are actively exploring the best approach, in close discussion with those organisations, and in consultation with community representatives.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","7419 ; 7420","2015-07-23T09:47:00.36Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390250/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390250/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390250/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-07-15","Languages: Assessments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if her Department will launch an immediate consultation into securing the future of examinations in (a) Turkish, (b) modern Greek and (c) other community languages.","false","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","7421"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390251","Department for Education","false","2015-07-21","<p>This government wants to see every child fulfilling their potential and succeeding in life.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Secretary of State for Work and Pensions recently announced that this government will focus on improving life chances by tackling the root causes of child poverty. It believes that action to ensure that parents can work and to improve educational attainment across the board will make the biggest difference to the lives of children, now and in the future. The Welfare Reform and Work Bill, introduced to Parliament on 9 July, includes a new statutory duty for government to report on these two key drivers of children’s life chances.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The government agrees with the view set out in the Independent Review that what happens before children start school is crucial in their development and later attainment. The Effective Pre-school, Primary and Secondary Education Project has shown a child has a greater chance of getting better exam results, and ultimately earning higher wages, by receiving pre-school education. That is why in 2010, the government extended the number of hours of free early education to which all three- and four-year-olds are entitled from 12.5 to 15 hours a week.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Since September 2013, the most disadvantaged two-year-olds across England have been able to access their 15-hour-a-week funded early learning place a year early. The Government has also introduced additional funding to support disadvantaged three and four year olds in early years settings through the Early Years Pupil Premium. This has been designed to close the gap at ages 3 and 4 between the additional support disadvantaged children get at age 2 through the free entitlement and the additional support they get in school through the school-age Pupil Premium.</p><p> </p><p>At the Budget, the Government reconfirmed its manifesto commitment to help hard-working families reduce the cost of childcare which will make it easier for parents to work if they would like to, knowing that their children are well cared for.</p><p> </p><p>The Government will set out more information about improving the life chances of children in a Life Chances Strategy in due course.</p><p> </p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2015-07-21T11:50:29.74Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390251/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390251/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390251/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-07-15","Poverty and Life Chances Review","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps she has taken in response to the recommendations of the Independent Review on Poverty and Life Chances, published in 2010.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","7422"
