"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390435","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-07-24","<p>A copy of form N20 Witness Summons (used in civil proceedings in the High Court, County Court and Court of Appeal), form PF25 Witness Summons (used in the Family Court)</p><p>form 5072 Witness Summons (used in the Crown Court) and Witness Summons (used in proceedings in the Magistrates’ Court) will be deposited in the Library of the House of Commons in due course.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2015-07-24T13:28:18.833Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390435/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390435/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390435/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-07-15","Witnesses","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if he will place in the Library a copy of the standard witness summons pro forma sent to complainants and witnesses to require them to attend court.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","7235"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390436","Leader of the House","false","2015-07-20","<p>The Government's proposals relate to the procedures of the House of Commons and are designed to be compatible with these. There is no selection process required for Legislative Grand Committees. All Members who represent constituencies in the relevant nations would be able to serve on the Legislative Grand Committees, whose role it would be to give consent to certified bills or provisions after Report Stage.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2015-07-20T15:18:25.2Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390436/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390436/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390436/answer",,,,,"34","Leader of the House","Leader of the House","2015-07-15","English Votes for English Laws","1","House of Commons","To ask the Leader of the House, what assessment he has made of the comparability of the method of selection of members to the legislative Grand Committee as set out in the proposed Standing Orders on English votes on English laws with selection processes for bodies performing the same functions in the devolved administrations.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian C. Lucas","7232"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390437","Leader of the House","false","2015-07-20","<p>The proposals have been published and it is open to all with an interest to consider the proposals and express views on them before they are put to the House of Commons for a decision. I have met colleagues who represent constituencies in Wales and I am happy to have further such conversations.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2015-07-20T15:15:05.04Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390437/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390437/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390437/answer",,,,,"34","Leader of the House","Leader of the House","2015-07-15","English Votes for English Laws: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Leader of the House, whether he plans to consult the public in Wales on his proposals for English votes on English laws.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian C. Lucas","7184"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390438","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-07-22","<p>The Department of Culture, Media and Sport is responsible for taking forward work on digital infrastructure and leads on reform of the Electronic Communications Code.</p><p>The Secretary of State for Culture Media and Sport and the Minister for Culture and the Digital Economy regularly meet with mobile network operators.</p><p>The Government is committed to reform of the Electronic Communications Code and intends to bring forward legislation in this area as soon as possible.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers","7183","2015-07-22T16:05:11.07Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390438/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390438/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390438/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-07-15","Telecommunications: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, whether she has had discussions with the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport on reform of the Electronic Communications Code.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian C. Lucas","7234"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390439","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-07-20","<p>With certain limited exceptions, energy is a devolved matter. It is therefore for the Northern Ireland Executive to decide whether or not they end subsidies to onshore wind projects and consider the funding implications.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2015-07-20T14:29:20.107Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390439/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390439/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390439/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-07-15","Wind Power: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what discussions she has had with Ministers from the Northern Ireland Executive on the implications for the Executive's funding of its decision not to end subsidies to onshore wind farms by April 2016.","false","Biography information for Sammy Wilson","East Antrim","Sammy Wilson","7236"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390440","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-07-22","<p>The Department of Culture, Media and Sport is responsible for taking forward work on digital infrastructure and leads on reform of the Electronic Communications Code.</p><p>The Secretary of State for Culture Media and Sport and the Minister for Culture and the Digital Economy regularly meet with mobile network operators.</p><p>The Government is committed to reform of the Electronic Communications Code and intends to bring forward legislation in this area as soon as possible.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers","7234","2015-07-22T16:05:10.96Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390440/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390440/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390440/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-07-15","Telecommunications: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, whether she has had discussions with mobile network operators on (a) digital infrastructure and inclusion and (b) reform of the Electronic Communications Code since May 2015.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian C. Lucas","7183"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390441","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-07-20","<p>The Belfast Agreement set out the arrangements governing the operation of democratic institutions in Northern Ireland, as well as British-Irish institutions and the North-South Ministerial Council. The subsequent St Andrews Agreement made changes to the operation of those institutions, as agreed by political parties representing a majority of unionist and nationalist opinion in Northern Ireland.</p><p>Both Agreements have been substantially delivered, though there remain some areas where a lack of consensus means that full implementation has not been possible.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2015-07-20T10:56:45.627Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390441/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390441/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390441/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-07-15","Belfast Agreement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, which parts of the Belfast Agreement have yet to be implemented; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Lady Hermon","North Down","Lady Hermon","7509"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390442","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-07-20","<p>The Public Processions Act (NI) 1998 empowers the Parades Commission for Northern Ireland to make determinations in relation to sensitive parades and parades related protests in Northern Ireland, independently of Government.</p><p>As I have pointed out many times publicly and in private meetings, Commission decisions are legally binding and it is incumbent upon everyone to abide by the rule of law.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2015-07-20T10:58:24.44Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390442/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390442/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390442/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-07-15","Parades Commission","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what steps she is taking to ensure that the determinations of the Parades Commission are accepted by all affected parties; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Lady Hermon","North Down","Lady Hermon","7510"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390443","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-07-20","<p>I meet regularly with Cabinet Ministers to discuss a range of issues.</p><p>As the Secretary of State for Transport has said on a number of occasions, the Government will now carefully consider all of the evidence in the Airports Commission’s Final Report before making a decision on the way forward. The Government will not therefore be commenting on the Airports Commission’s recommendations until it has had time to examine the evidence. However, the Government recognises the need to make a decision as soon as we can, after considering all relevant matters.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2015-07-20T12:18:47.397Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390443/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390443/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390443/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-07-15","Aviation: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what discussions she has had with the Secretary of State for Transport about the implications of the Davies Report on the UK's airport strategy for Northern Ireland; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Lady Hermon","North Down","Lady Hermon","7513"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390444","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-07-20","<p>Since my appointment as Secretary of State for Northern Ireland in September 2012, I have met the Chair of the Parades Commission on ten occasions.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2015-07-20T10:59:40.237Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390444/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390444/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390444/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-07-15","Parades Commission","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, how many meetings she has had with the Chairman of the Northern Ireland Parades Commission since first becoming Secretary of State for Northern Ireland; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Lady Hermon","North Down","Lady Hermon","7512"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390445","Prime Minister","false","2015-07-21","<p>I regularly visit all parts of the United Kingdom. My last visit to Northern Ireland was in April.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron",,"2015-07-21T14:44:49.727Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390445/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390445/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390445/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2015-07-15","Domestic Visits: North Down","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, what plans he has to visit North Down constituency; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Lady Hermon","North Down","Lady Hermon","7511"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390446","Cabinet Office","false","2015-07-20","<p>The OECD collects data on enforcement from all 41 members of the convention on bribery of foreign public officials. Transparency International’s ‘Exporting Corruption’ report, last published in December 2014, ranked the UK as an ‘active enforcer’ against foreign bribery, together with Germany, the United States of America and Switzerland.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2015-07-20T16:18:44.067Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390446/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390446/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390446/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-07-15","Public Service: Corruption","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, with reference to the Prime Minister's article in the Huffington Post, published on 6 June 2015, what the source is for the Prime Minister's statement that the OECD has judged the UK to be one of only four countries globally which actively pursues bribery of foreign public officials.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","7514"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390447","Prime Minister","false","2015-07-20","<p>It has been the practice of successive Governments not to disclose information relating to internal discussions.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron",,"2015-07-20T14:24:57.01Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390447/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390447/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390447/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2015-07-15","Health Professions: Regulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, what discussions he has had with (a) Ministers, (b) special advisers and (c) officials in the Department of Health on bringing forward the draft Law Commission Bill on regulation of health and social care professions for consideration by Parliament; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","7478"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390448","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-07-22","<p>According to Ofcom only 3% of premises in the UK had access to speeds of less than 2Mbps in June 2014 (down from 11% in 2010). The government estimates that by the end of 2015 this will be around 1% as a result of the BDUK broadband programme.</p><p> </p><p>The government will ensure that the remaining premises have access to speeds of at least 2Mbps by the end of 2015 by making available the option of satellite broadband connections, which will have the capability of delivering superfast speeds for those who want it.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-07-22T09:30:54.177Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390448/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390448/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390448/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-07-15","Telecommunications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps the Government is taking to ensure that all households have access to efficient digital communication networks and that broadband is available to all households at data transfer rates greater than 2 Mbit/s before the end of 2015.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","7195"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390449","Prime Minister","false","2015-07-21","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the press release published by the Cabinet Office and Scotland Office on 22 May 2015, which can be accessed via the gov.uk website.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron",,"2015-07-21T14:23:39.897Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390449/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390449/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390449/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2015-07-15","SG First Minister: Diplomatic Relations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, which current Ministers were aware of the content of the memorandum written by a Scotland Office civil servant on 6 March 2015, containing an account of the meeting between the Scottish First Minister and the French Ambassador before it was leaked to the press.","false","Biography information for Peter Grant","Glenrothes","Peter Grant","7415"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390450","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-20","<p /> <p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on the 16<sup>th</sup> July 2015 to Question <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=6682" target="_blank">UIN 6682</a>.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-07-20T13:18:04.923Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390450/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390450/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390450/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-15","Work Capability Assessment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer from the Prime Minister of 24 June 2015, Official Report, columns 885-6, when he expects numbers of deaths of people declared fit to work and related standardised mortality ratios to be published.","false","Biography information for Debbie Abrahams","Oldham East and Saddleworth","Debbie Abrahams","7362"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390451","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-07-23","<p>Royal Mail was privatised in October 2013. Regardless of ownership, Royal Mail as the designated Universal Service Provider for the United Kingdom is required to deliver the universal postal service in accordance with minimum requirements set by Parliament and quality of service standards set by Ofcom, the postal services regulator.</p><p> </p><p>Royal Mail publishes reports on its quality of service each quarter on its website. Ofcom closely monitors Royal Mail’s quality of service to ensure that service standards are maintained throughout the country.</p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2015-07-23T10:48:44.927Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390451/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390451/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390451/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-07-15","Postal Services: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what assessment he has made of the effect of the privatisation of Royal Mail on (a) residential properties and (b) businesses in Scotland.","false","Biography information for Margaret Ferrier","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Margaret Ferrier","7407"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390452","Scotland Office","false","2015-07-21","<p>A variety of events have been hosted in Dover House, both by Scotland Office Ministers and by third parties. Events are aimed at engaging stakeholders on a wide variety of policy issues and aspects of life in Scotland.</p><p>Since I was appointed Secretary of State for Scotland in May 2015 there have been five events hosted by non-government bodies at Dover House.</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2015-07-21T10:43:46.887Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390452/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390452/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390452/answer","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390452/answer/previousversion/16065","Biography information for David Mundell","2","Scotland","Scotland","2015-07-15","Dover House","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, how many events have been hosted by non-government bodies at Dover House since he assumed his current appointment.","false","Biography information for Margaret Ferrier","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Margaret Ferrier","7426"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390453","Scotland Office","false","2015-07-21","<p>The Government has amended the EU Referendum Bill so the referendum will not be held on 5 May 2016.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2015-07-21T10:44:57.47Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390453/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390453/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390453/answer","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390453/answer/previousversion/16067","Biography information for David Mundell","2","Scotland","Scotland","2015-07-15","UK Membership of EU: Referendums","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what discussions he has had with Ministers from the Scottish Government on the implications of holding a referendum on the UK's membership of the EU on the same day as the elections to the Scottish Parliament.","false","Biography information for Margaret Ferrier","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Margaret Ferrier","7427"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390454","Scotland Office","false","2015-08-04","<p>I have regular discussions with the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport on a wide range of issues. The Government is committed to reforming the current Code in ways that will promote network connectivity, expand coverage and take into account the legitimate interests of all parties. By enabling the rollout of telecommunications infrastructure, Code reform will provide more consumers across the country with a range of high quality digital services.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2015-08-04T08:46:32.99Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390454/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390454/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390454/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2015-07-15","Telecommunications: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, whether he has had discussions with the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport on reform of the Electronic Communications Code.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian C. Lucas","7233"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390455","Scotland Office","false","2015-08-04","<p>Responsibility for engagement on these issues is led by my Rt hon Friend the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport who regularly meets with all stakeholders across the telecoms industry to discuss a variety of relevant issues, including the reform of the Electronic Communications Code.</p><p>The Government is committed to reforming the current Code in ways that will promote network connectivity, expand coverage and take into account the legitimate interests of all parties. By enabling the rollout of telecommunications infrastructure, Code reform will provide more consumers across the country with a range of high quality digital services.</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2015-08-04T08:44:07.83Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390455/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390455/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390455/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2015-07-15","Telecommunications: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, whether he has had discussions with mobile network operators on (a) digital infrastructure and inclusion and (b) reform of the Electronic Communications Code since May 2015.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian C. Lucas","7185"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390456","Scotland Office","false","2015-07-21","<p>The Scottish Parliament will be one of the most powerful devolved legislatures in the world once the Scotland Bill is enacted. Compared to the average position of sub-central governments within the OECD, the Scottish Parliament will be among the most powerful in terms of tax and spending powers just behind Canadian provinces and Swiss cantons, and ahead of devolved legislatures in Australian states and German Länder.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2015-07-21T10:50:36.367Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390456/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390456/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390456/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2015-07-15","Devolution: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, pursuant to his contribution in the House on 8 June 2015, Official Report, column 926, what comparative assessment he has made of the scope of powers devolved to the Scottish Parliament, if the Scotland Bill is passed, and comparable European and North American legislatures.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","7228"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390457","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-20","<p>June 2015 was the first time the Secretary of State received advice that major projects should be paused in order to protect the public purse and to allow the programme to be reset.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-07-20T15:45:05.173Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390457/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390457/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390457/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-07-15","Network Rail","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, with reference to Network Rail's Board minutes of 19 March 2015, when the Chief Executive of Network Rail first raised with him the need to take a decision on the deferral of enhanced projects.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","7273"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390458","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-20","<p>I refer the Honourable Member to my answer on 13 July 2015, UIN 6150</p><p><a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=6150" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=6150</a>.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-07-20T15:49:00.71Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390458/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390458/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390458/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-07-15","Network Rail","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, on what dates he has met the Chief Executive of Network Rail since 1 January 2015.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","7274"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390459","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-20","<p>On 25<sup>th</sup> June the Secretary of State announced that work on Midland Main Line electrification was being paused pending Sir Peter Hendy’s proposals this autumn on re-planning the Control Period 5 programme, at which point the Secretary of State will make a statement to the House. It would be premature to speculate now on the outcome of the re-plan.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-07-20T14:52:05.287Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390459/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390459/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390459/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-07-15","Midland Main Railway Line: Electrification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when he expects work on the electrification of the Midland Mainline to resume; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Amanda Solloway","Derby North","Amanda Solloway","7216"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390460","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-20","<p>The Driver and Vehicle Licensing Agency (DVLA) takes the protection and security of its data very seriously. A comprehensive set of safeguards is in place to ensure data is disclosed only where it is lawful and fair to do so.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Individuals may write to the DVLA to request that their personal information is not disclosed if it would cause unwarranted and substantial damage or distress. The DVLA does not operate a blanket opt-out process but considers each such request taking into account the individual’s particular circumstances.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-07-20T13:40:13.983Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390460/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390460/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390460/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-07-15","Driver and Vehicle Licensing Agency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what mechanisms exist to allow vehicle owners to opt out of having their details sold to private sector organisations by the DVLA.","false","Biography information for Margaret Ferrier","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Margaret Ferrier","7425"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390461","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-21","<p>No assessment has been made of the effect of the operation of Class 313 trains on Southern services from Hove Station to West Coastway destinations on passenger satisfaction levels. However Transport Focus, who consult more than 50,000 passengers a year to produce the National Rail Passenger Survey, provide a network-wide picture of passengers' satisfaction with rail travel.</p><p>The latest figures, from the Spring 2015 survey (<a href="http://data.transportfocus.org.uk/train/nps/question/service-overall/" target="_blank">http://data.transportfocus.org.uk/train/nps/question/service-overall/</a>) show that 76% of passengers were satisfied with their journey on Southern’s Sussex Coast route, which incorporates the West Coastway services.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-07-21T15:45:03.93Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390461/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390461/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390461/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-07-15","Railways: South East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the effect of the operation of Class 313 trains on Southern services from Hove Station to West Coastway destinations on passenger satisfaction levels.","false","Biography information for Peter Kyle","Hove","Peter Kyle","7414"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390462","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-21","<p>We are aware of two complaints from Southern’s customers, and two letters from honourable Members, about the lack of toilet facilities on Class 313 trains that run services between Hove and West Coastway stations since their introduction in 2010.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-07-21T15:41:44.867Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390462/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390462/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390462/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-07-15","Railways: South East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many complaints his Department has received from customers about the lack of toilet facilities on Class 313 trains that run services between Hove and West Coastway stations since their introduction in 2010.","false","Biography information for Peter Kyle","Hove","Peter Kyle","7413"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390463","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-21","<p>The rolling stock operated by individual train operators is a detailed operational matter for them. They must decide what rolling stock is deployed on particular routes and services. Govia Thameslink Railway, the operator of the Thameslink, Southern and Great Northern franchise into which Southern services merge on 26 July 2015, has included no plans to replace this fleet on the West Coastway.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-07-21T15:38:34.4Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390463/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390463/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390463/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-07-15","Railways: South East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when the Class 313 trains in operation on Southern's West Coastway services will be replaced with newer rolling stock.","false","Biography information for Peter Kyle","Hove","Peter Kyle","7412"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390464","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-21","<p>The North of England Electrification Task Force took account of the estimated wider economic benefits of electrification in drawing up its recommendations on the priorities for future electrification of lines in the North of England, published in March 2015. Network Rail is taking these recommendations into account in assessing the case for further electrification of the national rail network, including the Leeds-Harrogate-York line. It plans to publish a draft update to the industry electrification strategy in due course.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-07-21T14:51:45.473Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390464/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390464/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390464/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-07-15","Railways: Yorkshire and the Humber","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the potential effect on employment in Yorkshire of the electrification of the Leeds-Harrogate-York railway line.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","7401"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390465","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-20","<p>The meeting focused on the operational performance of the railway and how it is serving the needs of passengers, including the industry’s readiness to manage services and communications to passengers during the engineering works planned at Easter, but it did not discuss issues around the cost or programming of the enhancement programme itself.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-07-20T14:32:48.26Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390465/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390465/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390465/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-07-15","Railways: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 2 July 2015 to Question 4668, whether cost overruns and potential delays on Network Rail's enhancement programme were discussed at the Performance Delivery Group meeting of 24 March 2015.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","7369"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390466","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-20","<p>All road users benefit from clear directions, including HGV drivers. It is clearly not in the interests of HGV drivers to rely upon inaccurate information, which may make them late or even involve them in accidents. Nevertheless, we believe that legislation would be a costly, bureaucratic and inappropriate way of dealing with the problem. Instead we have made significant efforts to link together freight associations, local authorities and satnav companies to ensure that HGV drivers are aware of the issue and have the latest information available to them.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Councils already have the means to set height and weight restrictions for roads, which are enforced by the police, and HGV satnav devices increasingly include up-to-date routing information that takes account of such restrictions.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Decisions on all aspects of traffic management policy are the responsibility of local traffic authorities, and how they and the police enforce this once they are in place it is a matter for them. We believe the necessary enforcement powers are available for this.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","7365","2015-07-20T14:46:34.697Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390466/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390466/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390466/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-07-15","Large Goods Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if his Department will bring forward legislative proposals to require heavy goods vehicles satellite navigation system providers to remove weight-restricted roads from their routes.","false","Biography information for Mrs Pauline Latham","Mid Derbyshire","Pauline Latham","7366"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390467","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-21","<p>To ensure our long term connectivity needs can be met, the previous Government established the independent Airports Commission to identify and recommend to Government options for maintaining this country’s status as an international hub for aviation. Three options for expansion were shortlisted by the Commission for further examination.</p><p>The Airports Commission has discussed and consulted on how airports outside the South East might be affected by expansion at the shortlisted expansion options. The relevant documents can be found on the Airports Commission website: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/airports-commission" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/airports-commission</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Commission’s final report was published on 01 July 2015. The Government will not be commenting on the any of the Airports Commission’s recommendations until it has had time to examine all the evidence.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-07-21T14:46:48.217Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390467/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390467/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390467/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-07-15","Leeds-Bradford Airport","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment his Department has made of the potential effect on Leeds-Bradford Airport of a new runway at (a) Heathrow and (b) Gatwick Airport.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","7399"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390468","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-20","<p>All road users benefit from clear directions, including HGV drivers. It is clearly not in the interests of HGV drivers to rely upon inaccurate information, which may make them late or even involve them in accidents. Nevertheless, we believe that legislation would be a costly, bureaucratic and inappropriate way of dealing with the problem. Instead we have made significant efforts to link together freight associations, local authorities and satnav companies to ensure that HGV drivers are aware of the issue and have the latest information available to them.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Councils already have the means to set height and weight restrictions for roads, which are enforced by the police, and HGV satnav devices increasingly include up-to-date routing information that takes account of such restrictions.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Decisions on all aspects of traffic management policy are the responsibility of local traffic authorities, and how they and the police enforce this once they are in place it is a matter for them. We believe the necessary enforcement powers are available for this.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","7366","2015-07-20T14:46:34.793Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390468/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390468/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390468/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-07-15","Large Goods Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if his Department will make an assessment of whether the powers local councils and police have to enforce restrictions on heavy goods vehicles driving on weight-restricted roads are sufficient to protect rural roads and surrounding environments.","false","Biography information for Mrs Pauline Latham","Mid Derbyshire","Pauline Latham","7365"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390469","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-21","<p>On 25 June I announced that officials had been instructed to begin work on the secondary legislation required to commence the relevant section of the Infrastructure Act. The Government then intends to announce a Cycling and Walking Investment Strategy as soon as is practicable, once all activities deemed necessary have been undertaken.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-07-21T14:04:36.657Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390469/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390469/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390469/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-07-15","Cycling: Capital Investment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what progress his Department has made on preparing the Cycling and Walking Investment Strategy for England.","false","Biography information for Ian Austin","Dudley North","Ian Austin","7331"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390470","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-21","<p>Operation Stack is the appropriate contingency arrangement to put in place when there is disruption to cross-channel traffic and is led by the Kent Police. It remains a last, not first, resort. The Department has not made any assessment of the effect of Operation Stack on the UK balance of trade, as any impact stems from the disruption to services – which this Government is determined to see resolved as soon as possible.</p><p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p>European Gateway Group is reviewing short and longer term solutions to traffic management in Kent, including Operation Stack, and will report back to the Department. When this review is completed the Department will analyse their findings and decide how to respond to their recommendations.</p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-07-21T14:08:50.603Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390470/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390470/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390470/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-07-15","M20: Large Goods Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will make it his policy to end Operation Stack; and whether his Department has made an assessment of the effect of that operation on the UK balance of trade.","false","Biography information for Mr Douglas Carswell","Clacton","Mr Douglas Carswell","7325"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390471","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-20","<p>Network Rail will consider the case for closure of level crossings on the East Coast Main Line during Control Period 5 alongside other schemes to reduce risk at level crossings on the network.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-07-20T15:52:46.247Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390471/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390471/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390471/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-07-15","East Coast Railway Line: Level Crossings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 14 July 2015 to Question 6464, how many of the 73 East Coast Main Line level crossings Network Rail plans to close during Control Period 5.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","7295"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390472","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-21","<p>Operation Stack is led by Kent police, with the support of all other emergency services, Highways England, Kent County Council, and many other key partners. Steps taken to mitigate the latest Calais disruption include:</p><p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p><ul><li>Providing additional resources to monitor the strategic and local network and to keep the agreed diversion routes clear.</li></ul></p><p> </p><p><ul><li>Agreed joint communications to inform customers of the current situation, including communications to keep freight on the M20 and within the Operation Stack phases.</li></ul></p><p> </p><p><ul><li>Identified, designed and implemented additional phases to Operation Stack as the situation has continued.</li></ul></p><p> </p><p><ul><li>Provided additional traffic management in Kent at roundabouts.</li></ul></p><p> </p><p><ul><li>Review and enhance the　current Signs and Signal Policy relating to Operation Stack.</li></ul></p><p> </p><p><ul><li>Kent County Council staff have been issuing bottles of water and food.</li></ul></p><p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p>The Government is looking to all parties, including Eurotunnel and Port of Dover, Kent County and Local Councils, Kent Police and the Highways England to play their part in working towards, implementing and then reviewing and managing the various solutions.</p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-07-21T14:37:50.187Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390472/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390472/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390472/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-07-15","M20: Large Goods Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps his Department is taking to mitigate the effects of Operation Stack on motorists in Kent.","false","Biography information for Gareth Johnson","Dartford","Gareth Johnson","7441"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390473","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-20","<p>The EU drivers’ hours rules (Regulation (EC) 561/2006) requires Member States to lay down their own rules for vehicles used for the carriage of passengers on regular routes where the route covered does not exceed 50km. In GB, the domestic drivers' hours rules (contained in the Transport Act 1968) meet this requirement.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-07-20T14:36:32.987Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390473/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390473/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390473/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-07-15","Bus Services: Working Hours","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what his policy is on implementation of EU rules on domestic bus driving hours.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","7460"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390474","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-21","<p>The Driver and Vehicle Licensing Agency (DVLA) remains open to further discussions with the Public and Commercial Services (PCS) union. An offer of further talks involving the Advisory, Conciliation and Arbitration Service (ACAS) was made to PCS on 16 July. The DVLA would welcome this approach and would like to pursue further dialogue with ACAS support.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-07-21T14:12:52.133Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390474/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390474/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390474/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-07-15","Driver and Vehicle Licensing Agency: Industrial Disputes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps he is taking to resolve the industrial dispute at the DVLA.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","7448"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390475","Wales Office","false","2015-07-22","<p>The Government is committed to delivering a reformed Electronic Communications Code that works for site providers, Code Operators, and ensures consumers have a choice of high quality telecommunications services. I have met with the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport and the Minister for Culture and the Digital Economy, to discuss improvements to digital infrastructure across Wales.</p><p> </p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2015-07-22T10:26:12.503Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390475/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390475/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390475/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2015-07-15","Telecommunications: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, whether he has had discussions with the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport on the reform of the Electronic Communications Code.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian C. Lucas","7200"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390476","Wales Office","false","2015-07-22","<p>Since May 2015, I have met with Three, to discuss the Electronic Communications Code and improvements to digital infrastructure, including mobile coverage across Wales.</p><p>This follows a programme of meetings with Mobile Network Operators and broadcasters in the last Parliament on issues such as the Electronic Communications Code and mobile not-spots in Wales.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2015-07-22T10:27:53.64Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390476/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390476/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/390476/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2015-07-15","Telecommunications: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, whether he has had discussions with mobile network operators on (a) digital infrastructure and inclusion and (b) reform of the Electronic Communications Code since May 2015.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian C. Lucas","7173"
